        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3546295408" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7572837352741223370">[3.5] Greene is always a pleasure to read and I enjoyed his sharp portrayal of a claustrophobic West African colony and its burdened citizens. But the heart of the matter here eludes me. Long-suffering Scobie&apos;s love affair with Helen felt implausible and childish. He relates to her as if she is a punishment. His Catholicism causes more pain. There must be an allegory happening here that is over my head. But Greene writes so well!</span>
  <span id="freeText7572837352741223370" style="display:none">[3.5] Greene is always a pleasure to read and I enjoyed his sharp portrayal of a claustrophobic West African colony and its burdened citizens. But the heart of the matter here eludes me. Long-suffering Scobie's love affair with Helen felt implausible and childish. He relates to her as if she is a punishment. His Catholicism causes more pain. There must be an allegory happening here that is over my head. But Greene writes so well!</span>
